athAndDetachesVirtualMachine()]\\ndisplay-name: mainAttachesAgentFromNativePathAndDetachesVirtualMachine()\\n]]></system-out>\\n</testcase>\\n<testcase name=\\\"test()\\\" classname=\\\"io_projectreactor_tools.blockhound.BlockhoundTest\\\" time=\\\"0\\\">\\n<system-out><![CDATA[\\nunique-id: [engine:junit-jupiter]/[class:io_projectreactor_tools.blockhound.BlockhoundTest]/[method:test()]\\ndisplay-name: test()\\n]]></system-out>\\n</testcase>\\n<system-out><![CDATA[\\nunique-id: [engine:junit-jupiter]\\ndisplay-name: JUnit Jupiter\\n]]></system-out>\\n</testsuite>\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_127\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"Using the `fix-missing-reachability-metadata` skill. I’m checking the current worktree state and the existing BlockHound changes first so I can continue from the prior attempt instead of redoing analysis.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_128\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge8/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/4784-9075b16a/skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_128\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge8/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/4784-9075b16a/skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"---\\nname: fix-missing-reachability-metadata\\ndescription: Fix missing GraalVM reachability metadata for a specific library. Use when the user asks to fix or add metadata because required metadata is missing and tests or native-image runs fail with missing metadata errors.\\n---\\n\\n# Fix missing reachability metadata entries in the reachability-metadata.json\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nRun a reproduce-fix-verify loop for missing metadata errors. Keep running the target test until it passes with no new missing metadata entries.\\n\\nLibrary coordinates should be provided in the prompt in the format `group:artifact:version`. If you are not sure what the coordinates are, ask the user.\\n\\n## Workflow\\n\\n1. Reproduce the failure:\\n   - Run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<coordinates>` from repository root.\\n2. Capture the missing metadata from the error message:\\n   - Locate any `Missing*RegistrationError` (e.g. `MissingReflectionRegistrationError`, `MissingResourceRegistrationError`, or any other variant).\\n   - Copy the suggested JSON entry for the missing type into the corresponding section of the reachability-metadata.\\n3. Choose the target file and insert the entry:\\n   - Write to `metadata/<library-specific-metadata-directory>/reachability-metadata.json`.\\n   - Keep valid JSON and avoid duplicating an existing equivalent entry. If the type already exists but a method or field is missing, add only that method or field.\\n4. Add the missing `condition` field:\\n   - Infer it from the error stack trace.\\n   - Set the `condition` field to `{ \\\"typeReached\\\": \\\"<class>\\\" }`, where `<class>` is the first class on the stack trace whose package shares the leading namespace with the tested library's package.\\n   - Package overlap can be partial, full package equality is not required.\\n   - Example: tested library's group `org.hibernate.orm...` and the class from a stack trace `org.hibernate.resource...` is a valid match.\\n\\n5. Verify and iterate:\\n   - Run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<coordinates>` again.\\n   - If another missing entry appears, repeat from step 2.\\n   - Finish only when the test run succeeds.\\n\\n## Error Patterns\\n\\nUse this reference when deriving the missing entry and condition.\\n\\n### Missing Registration Entry Pattern\\n\\nExample error shape:\\n\\n```text\\nCaused by: org.graalvm.nativeimage.MissingReflectionRegistrationError:\\nCannot reflectively invoke constructor 'public org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator()'\\n...\\nadd the following to the 'reflection' section of reachability-metadata.json:\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator\\\",\\n  \\\"methods\\\": [{ \\\"name\\\": \\\"<init>\\\", \\\"parameterTypes\\\": [] }]\\n}\\n...\\nat org.hibernate.boot.model.internal.GeneratorBinder.instantiateGeneratorViaDefaultConstructor(...)\\nat org.hibernate.resource.beans.internal.Helper$2.produceBeanInstance(...)\\n```\\n\\n### Condition Inference\\n\\nFor missing type `org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator`, a valid condition class is:\\n\\n`org.hibernate.boot.model.internal.GeneratorBinder`\\n\\nReason: both share the leading namespace `org.hibernate`, which is sufficient for this workflow.\\n\\n## Environment Troubleshooting\\n\\n- If failures look unrelated or tooling looks inconsistent, verify both `JAVA_HOME` and `GRAALVM_HOME` point to a compatible GraalVM JDK distribution.\\n- If they are not set to GraalVM, ask the user to provide the correct GraalVM distribution path and retry.\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_129\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' tests/src/io.projectreactor.tools/blockhound/1.0.8.RELEASE/src/test/java/io_projectreactor_tools/blockhound/LambdaFactoryTest.java\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_129\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' tests/src/io.projectreactor.tools/blockhound/1.0.8.RELEASE/src/test/java/io_projectreactor_tools/blockhound/LambdaFactoryTest.java\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage io_projectreactor_tools.blockhound;\\n\\nimport java.lang.instrument.ClassFileTransformer;\\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\\nimport java.security.ProtectionDomain;\\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\\nimport java.util.Collection;\\nimport java.util.Collections;\\nimport java.util.LinkedHashMap;\\nimport java.util.List;\\nimport java.util.Map;\\n\\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.parallel.ResourceLock;\\n\\nimport reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.agent.builder.LambdaFactory;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class LambdaFactoryTest {\\n    private static final String BYTE_BUDDY_EXPERIMENTAL_PROPERTY =\\n            \\\"reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.experimental\\\";\\n    private static final byte[] CLASS_BYTES = new byte[] {1, 2, 3, 4};\\n\\n    static {\\n        System.setProperty(BYTE_BUDDY_EXPERIMENTAL_PROPERTY, \\\"true\\\");\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    @ResourceLock(\\\"lambda-factory-transformers\\\")\\n    void registerAndReleaseTransformerThroughInjectedFactory() {\\n        ClassFileTransformer transformer = new NoOpClassFileTransformer();\\n        Dispatcher dispatcher = new Dispatcher();\\n\\n        try {\\n            boolean firstRegistration = LambdaFactory.register(transformer, dispatcher);\\n            assertThat(firstRegistration).isTrue();\\n        } catch (Error error) {\\n            printThrowable(error, 0);\\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\\n                throw error;\\n            }\\n            return;\\n        } catch (RuntimeException exception) {\\n            printThrowable(exception, 0);\\n            if (!isCausedByUnsupportedFeatureError(exception)) {\\n                throw exception;\\n            }\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        try {\\n            assertThat(LambdaFactory.release(transformer)).isTrue();\\n            assertThat(LambdaFactory.release(transformer)).isFalse();\\n        } catch (Error error) {\\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\\n                throw error;\\n            }\\n        } catch (RuntimeException exception) {\\n            if (!isCausedByUnsupportedFeatureError(exception)) {\\n                throw exception;\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    @ResourceLock(\\\"lambda-factory-transformers\\\")\\n    void makeDelegatesToRegisteredDispatcher() throws Exception {\\n        Map<ClassFileTransformer, LambdaFactory> previousFactories = new LinkedHashMap<>(\\n                LambdaFactory.CLASS_FILE_TRANSFORMERS);\\n        LambdaFactory.CLASS_FILE_TRANSFORMERS.clear();\\n\\n        try {\\n            ClassFileTransformer transformer = new NoOpClassFileTransformer();\\n            Dispatcher dispatcher = new Dispatcher();\\n            Method makeMethod = Dispatcher.class.getMethod(\\n                    \\\"make\\\",\\n                    Object.class,\\n                    String.class,\\n                    Object.class,\\n                    Object.class,\\n                    Object.class,\\n                    Object.class,\\n                    boolean.class,\\n                    List.class,\\n                    List.class,\\n                    Collection.class);\\n            LambdaFactory.CLASS_FILE_TRANSFORMERS.put(transformer, new LambdaFactory(dispatcher, makeMethod));\\n\\n            Object caller = new Object();\\n            Object invokedType = new Object();\\n            Object samMethodType = new Object();\\n            Object implMethod = new Object();\\n            Object instantiatedMethodType = new Object();\\n            List<Class<?>> markerInterfaces = Collections.singletonList(Runnable.class);\\n            List<Object> additionalBridges = Collections.singletonList(\\\"bridge\\\");\\n\\n            byte[] generatedBytes = LambdaFactory.make(\\n                    caller,\\n                    \\\"run\\\",\\n                    invokedType,\\n                    samMethodType,\\n                    implMethod,\\n                    instantiatedMethodType,\\n                    true,\\n                    markerInterfaces,\\n                    additionalBridges);\\n\\n            assertThat(generatedBytes).isSameAs(CLASS_BYTES);\\n            assertThat(dispatcher.invocations).hasSize(1);\\n            Invocation invocation = dispatcher.invocations.get(0);\\n            assertThat(invocation.caller).isSameAs(caller);\\n            assertThat(invocation.methodName).isEqualTo(\\\"run\\\");\\n            assertThat(invocation.invokedType).isSameAs(invokedType);\\n            assertThat(invocation.samMethodType).isSameAs(samMethodType);\\n            assertThat(invocation.implMethod).isSameAs(implMethod);\\n            assertThat(invocation.instantiatedMethodType).isSameAs(instantiatedMethodType);\\n            assertThat(invocation.serializable).isTrue();\\n            assertThat(invocation.markerInterfaces).isSameAs(markerInterfaces);\\n            assertThat(invocation.additionalBridges).isSameAs(additionalBridges);\\n            assertThat(invocation.classFileTransformers).containsExactly(transformer);\\n        } finally {\\n            LambdaFactory.CLASS_FILE_TRANSFORMERS.clear();\\n            LambdaFactory.CLASS_FILE_TRANSFORMERS.putAll(previousFactories);\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static boolean isCausedByUnsupportedFeatureError(Throwable throwable) {\\n        Throwable current = throwable.getCause();\\n        while (current != null) {\\n            if (current instanceof Error error && NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\\n                return true;\\n            }\\n            current = current.getCause();\\n        }\\n        return false;\\n    }\\n\\n    private static void printThrowable(Throwable throwable, int depth) {\\n        String indent = \\\"  \\\".repeat(depth);\\n        System.out.println(indent + throwable.getClass().getName() + \\\": \\\" + throwable.getMessage());\\n        for (Throwable suppressed : throwable.getSuppressed()) {\\n            System.out.println(indent + \\\"suppressed:\\\");\\n            printThrowable(suppressed, depth + 1);\\n        }\\n        Throwable cause = throwable.getCause();\\n        if (cause != null && cause != throwable) {\\n            System.out.println(indent + \\\"caused by:\\\");\\n            printThrowable(cause, depth + 1);\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    public static final class Dispatcher {\\n        private final List<Invocation> invocations = new ArrayList<>();\\n\\n        public byte[] make(Object caller, String methodName, Object invokedType, Object samMethodType,\\n                Object implMethod, Object instantiatedMethodType, boolean serializable,\\n                List<Class<?>> markerInterfaces, List<?> additionalBridges,\\n                Collection<ClassFileTransformer> classFileTransformers) {\\n            invocations.add(new Invocation(\\n                    caller,\\n                    methodName,\\n                    invokedType,\\n                    samMethodType,\\n                    implMethod,\\n                    instantiatedMethodType,\\n                    serializable,\\n                    markerInterfaces,\\n                    additionalBridges,\\n                    classFileTransformers));\\n            return CLASS_BYTES;\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class Invocation {\\n        private final Object caller;\\n        private final String methodName;\\n        private final Object invokedType;\\n        private final Object samMethodType;\\n        private final Object implMethod;\\n        private final Object instantiatedMethodType;\\n        private final boolean serializable;\\n        private final List<Class<?>> markerInterfaces;\\n        private final List<?> additionalBridges;\\n        private final Collection<ClassFileTransformer> classFileTransformers;\\n\\n        private Invocation(Object caller, String methodName, Object invokedType, Object samMethodType,\\n                Object implMethod, Object instantiatedMethodType, boolean serializable,\\n                List<Class<?>> markerInterfaces, List<?> additionalBridges,\\n                Collection<ClassFileTransformer> classFileTransformers) {\\n            this.caller = caller;\\n            this.methodName = methodName;\\n            this.invokedType = invokedType;\\n            this.samMethodType = samMethodType;\\n            this.implMethod = implMethod;\\n            this.instantiatedMethodType = instantiatedMethodType;\\n            this.serializable = serializable;\\n            this.markerInterfaces = markerInterfaces;\\n            this.additionalBridges = additionalBridges;\\n            this.classFileTransformers = classFileTransformers;\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class NoOpClassFileTransformer implements ClassFileTransformer {\\n        @Override\\n        public byte[] transform(ClassLoader loader, String className, Class<?> classBeingRedefined,\\n                ProtectionDomain protectionDomain, byte[] classfileBuffer) {\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_130\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' tests/src/io.projectreactor.tools/blockhound/1.0.8.RELEASE/build.gradle\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_130\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' tests/src/io.projectreactor.tools/blockhound/1.0.8.RELEASE/build.gradle\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and re